{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/addingdarktheme/","webpackCompilationHash":"cc8c95b39a6ecc80d03a","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1>Adding Dark Theme To The Project</h1>\n<br/>\nSo finally, I have added Dark mode to the project. \nWhile I really do not take care of my eyes, the whole idea of a dark screen with light fonts does fascinate me.\n<br/><br/>\n<hr/>\n<h2>Let me try to explain how I achieved the same in this blog</h2>\n<p>I have usedy Gatby as my starter pack to build this project, it is pretty simple to understand and implement it.\nI will try to explain a bit about how you all can go on about achieving the same. Once you have your boiler plate installed,\nyou just have to install another <code class=\"language-text\">Gatsby Plugin</code> and it is pretty much straight forward from there on.</p>\n<br/>\n<h4>main.css (rename it to mess.css?)</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">const themeLight =</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">--bg</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> white<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">--body</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> black<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">--textNormal</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> #222<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">--textTitle</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> #222<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token selector\">const themeDark =</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">--bg</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> #222831<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">--body</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> #eeeeee<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">--textNormal</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> #fff1c1<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">--textTitle</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> #fff1c1<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h4>Install</h4>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm install gatsby-plugin-dark-mode</code></p>\n<p>In your config.js:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">module<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>exports <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  plugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">'gatsby-plugin-dark-mode'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Usability</h3>\n<p>The plugin that you just installed allows you to access a component <code class=\"language-text\">ThemeToggler</code>.\nYou can pass your children components inside it.\nIt needs in 2 parameters : </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">- Your current {theme}  \n- a function : toggleTheme</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Implementation</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Import the {ThemeToggler} from <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-plugin-dark-mode</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Create a toggle button for the two themes</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>For every div you want to have the dark theme mode, give it the respective styling</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<br/>\n<p> <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 600px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f00a14e10cd2f09075fd84e62e0d3dfe/e49a9/darktheme.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Graph\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/f00a14e10cd2f09075fd84e62e0d3dfe/34e8a/darktheme.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f00a14e10cd2f09075fd84e62e0d3dfe/d4214/darktheme.png 150w,\n/static/f00a14e10cd2f09075fd84e62e0d3dfe/135ae/darktheme.png 300w,\n/static/f00a14e10cd2f09075fd84e62e0d3dfe/34e8a/darktheme.png 600w,\n/static/f00a14e10cd2f09075fd84e62e0d3dfe/e49a9/darktheme.png 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span> </p>\n<p> <em>Hey Apple, hire me please? I heard Jony Ive left?</em> </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token property\">PS</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> I have also changed the syntax highlighting theme. \nI might just write a blog explaining how to do that someday ?</code></pre></div>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/packages/gatsby-plugin-dark-mode/\" title=\"Gatsby Dark Mode Plugin\">Official Documentation</a></p>","frontmatter":{"date":"July 05, 2019","title":"Dark Theme"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/blog/addingdarktheme/"}}}